File: platform/plugin-tools/src/commands/build.ts around lines 1176-1217.

The problem: when a file change arrives during an active build, the watcher callback sets pendingRebuild=true (because building=true) AND starts a new debounceTimer. When the build finishes and sees pendingRebuild=true, it calls rebuild(). But the debounceTimer also fires independently, causing a second rebuild.

Fix: At the start of the rebuild() function (around line 1176), clear debounceTimer:
```typescript
const rebuild = async () => {
  if (debounceTimer) {
    clearTimeout(debounceTimer);
    debounceTimer = undefined;
  }
  building = true;
  // ... rest of rebuild
};
```

This ensures that when rebuild() runs (whether from debounce or pendingRebuild), any lingering timer is cancelled.

File: platform/shared/src/index.ts around lines 460-480 (the validateUrlPattern function).

The IP detection regex is at line 466-467:
```typescript
const ipMatch = host.match(/^\d{1,3}(\.\d{1,3}){3}(:\d+)?$/);
```

After this regex matches, add octet validation:
```typescript
if (ipMatch) {
  const hostWithoutPort = host.replace(/:\d+$/, '');
  const octets = hostWithoutPort.split('.').map(Number);
  if (octets.some(o => o > 255)) {
    return { valid: false, error: `Invalid IPv4 address in URL pattern: octets must be 0-255, got '${hostWithoutPort}'` };
  }
}
```

Test file: look for existing validateUrlPattern tests — check platform/shared/src/manifest.test.ts or platform/shared/src/index.test.ts or similar. Add test cases for valid and invalid IPs.
